Swing components don&#39;t know how to handle alpha based colors (ie `new Color(0,0,0,0)`), they are either transparent or opaque.

Instead, make use of `JComponent#setOpaque`.

Don&#39;t perform blocking or long running operations in paint methods.  Painting should be optimised to run as fast as possible, otherwise your risk making your program unresponsive and/or laggy.

Don&#39;t use `null` layouts, these are just going to continue to cause you issues.  Instead, make use of the layout management API instead.  See [Laying Out Components Within a Container](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/layout/index.html) for more details

