Using `java.time`, the modern date-time API:
--

**You do not need a `DateTimeFormatter`:** `java.time` API is based on [ISO 8601](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) and therefore you do not need a `DateTimeFormatter` to parse a date-time string which is already in ISO 8601 format e.g. your date string, `0001-03-10` which can be parsed directly into a `LocalDate` instance which contains just date units.

